00:06:18.010 --> 00:06:21.590
when two things that seem
very different on the surface

00:06:21.590 --> 00:06:24.089
seem to be different
reflections of the same thing.

00:06:24.089 --> 00:06:25.630
And then we know
we've made progress.

00:06:25.630 --> 00:06:27.046
And that pretty
well characterizes

00:06:27.046 --> 00:06:29.650
almost all the progress
in physics over the ages,

00:06:29.650 --> 00:06:31.237
from, for example,
in recent times,

00:06:31.237 --> 00:06:33.070
the recognition of
electricity to magnetism,

00:06:33.070 --> 00:06:35.890
which seemed so different, are
really exactly the same thing.

00:06:35.890 --> 00:06:39.040
One person's electricity is
another person's magnetism.

00:06:39.040 --> 00:06:41.410
That led to the realization
of space and time,

00:06:41.410 --> 00:06:43.664
which seemed different,
are really the same thing.

00:06:43.664 --> 00:06:45.080
And what one person
sees as space,

00:06:45.080 --> 00:06:46.840
another person will
measure as time.

00:06:46.840 --> 00:06:48.190
We live in a four-dimensional
universe, not

00:06:48.190 --> 00:06:49.540
a three-dimensional universe.

00:06:49.540 --> 00:06:52.390
And those kind of developments
have progressively

00:06:52.390 --> 00:06:54.340
